  "text": "In previous work, the aromatic L o preferring dye naphtopyrene was found to perturb the membrane around the miscibility transition temperature at concentrations of 0.3 mol% [CITATION_1] . A recent molecular dynamics study by Barnoud and coworkers [CITATION_2] indicated a difference between the effects of aromatic and aliphatic compounds. While aliphatic compounds induced mixing of a phaseseparating membrane, aromatic hydrocarbons stabilized the phase separation.",
